### tryParseAlign() {#a1381cfa5d5d20b2c0de03ce8f211c1cf}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static ParseRet anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;VFABIDemangler.cpp&#125;::tryParseAlign (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> &amp; ParseString, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/align">Align</a> &amp; Alignment)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Looks into the &lt;parameters&gt; part of the mangled name in search of a valid &#39;aligned&#39; clause.

The function should be invoked after parsing a parameter via <code>tryParseParameter</code>.

On success, it removes the parsed parameter from <code>ParseString</code>, sets <code>PKind</code> to the correspondent enum value, sets <code>StepOrPos</code> accordingly, and return success. On a syntax error, it return a parsing error. If nothing is parsed, it returns std::nullopt.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/vfabidemangler-cpp/#l00280">280</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/vfabidemangler-cpp">VFABIDemangler.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### tryParseCompileTimeLinearToken() {#a856e22af4413a5ea9df66d623f35b824}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static ParseRet anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;VFABIDemangler.cpp&#125;::tryParseCompileTimeLinearToken (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> &amp; ParseString, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#add480f2ed87faa59c16d4c01ffb4bf39">VFParamKind</a> &amp; PKind, int &amp; LinearStep, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Token)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
The function looks for the following strings at the beginning of the input string <code>ParseString</code>:

&lt;token&gt; &#123;&quot;n&quot;&#125; &lt;number&gt;

On success, it removes the parsed parameter from <code>ParseString</code>, sets <code>PKind</code> to the correspondent enum value, sets <code>LinearStep</code> to &lt;number&gt;, and return success. On a syntax error, it return a parsing error. If nothing is parsed, it returns std::nullopt.

The function expects &lt;token&gt; to be one of &quot;l&quot;, &quot;R&quot;, &quot;U&quot; or &quot;L&quot;.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/vfabidemangler-cpp/#l00185">185</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/vfabidemangler-cpp">VFABIDemangler.cpp</a>.

### tryParseVLEN() {#a14373b1995a870811ec0b24e8c7bb274}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static ParseRet anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;VFABIDemangler.cpp&#125;::tryParseVLEN (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> &amp; ParseString, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abe2c24a8dc2fb979e8e54e15f088169c">VFISAKind</a> ISA, std::pair&lt; unsigned, bool &gt; &amp; ParsedVF)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Extract the <code>&lt;vlen&gt;</code> information from the mangled string, and sets <code>ParsedVF</code> accordingly.

A <code>&lt;vlen&gt; == &quot;x&quot;</code> token is interpreted as a scalable vector length and the boolean is set to true, otherwise a nonzero unsigned integer will be directly used as a VF. On success, the <code>&lt;vlen&gt;</code> token is removed from the input string <code>ParseString</code>.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/vfabidemangler-cpp/#l00080">80</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/vfabidemangler-cpp">VFABIDemangler.cpp</a>.
